cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE

This paper deals with tabling, a technique commonly used in logic programming, and extends it to support rational terms. This makes it likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications of rational terms in constraint handling systems and coinduction, which makes it relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper describes the implementation of the extension and compares it with current coinductive transformations, which makes it relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
